Class FrameInterval.StepwiseInterval

java.lang.Object
  au.edu.jcu.v4l4j.FrameInterval.StepwiseInterval
Enclosing class:
FrameInterval
public static class FrameInterval.StepwiseInterval
extends java.lang.Object

A continuous frame interval is a bounded frame interval. It has minimum, maximum and step values, all expressed as numerator/denominator pairs contained in a FrameInterval.DiscreteInterval object. A continuous interval object encapsulates the bounds for a continuous frame interval.

gilles
